The course provides an overview of the ethical and legal challenges of AI systems, (smart) robots and the  (European) legal framework, especially the AI Act.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Rapid progress in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and robotics (often operating with a form of AI) is challenging the traditional boundaries of law. AI systems are widely employed to make decisions that have an increasingly far-reaching impact on individuals and society. 
This course examines the opportunities, but also the challenges of AI systems to the existing (European) legal order. Moreover, it provides an analysis of the recently adopted Artificial Intelligence Act of the European Union as well as several key initiatives at the international levels on AI ethics and regulation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course, students who have passed the subject will have knowledge and understanding of:  - the recent technological developments in the field of AI and robotics; - the most urgent ethical and legal issues raised by the use of AI systems and (smart) robotics; - applicable legislation, concepts, principles and regulation of AI systems and robotics within the European regulatory framework, especially the AI Act, and the case law of the Court of Justice of the European Union and the European Court of Human Rights in the relevant fields; - key initiatives at the international levels on AI ethics and regulation; - how to analyse legal questions regarding AI and robotics as well as understanding the economic, political and social implications of these technologies.
